      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2023-07-03T07:09:31.238Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Yeah some trainers do fine with 20/10 in ERG but many struggle to change fast enough.  20/10 is the borderline between ERG and slope or resistance effectiveness.</p>\n<p>I like slope mode but really there is not much difference between slope and resistance other than we have auto slope mode which can help doing intervals like 20/10 because it can automatically change slopes so you don\u2019t need to shift so much.  Slope is just like a hill outdoors.  Meaning you control the intensity via cadence and gears.</p>\n<p>This article explains it better<br>\n<a href=\"https://blog.trainerday.com/smart-slopes-779c74a0c921\" class=\"onebox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">https://blog.trainerday.com/smart-slopes-779c74a0c921</a></p>\n<p>Hope that helps.</p>",
